race.comment: All but the top weight are rising in distance. PRETTY PLEASE (6) brings a strong Maiden win from the Sapphire Coast over a mile heavily bet. Presented off narrow defeats at Kembla Grange, and they also stack up for this. She's a strong finisher, and the step up to the middle distance is ideal. She just missed at Canberra in a CL1, the only time she raced at 2000m. STAR EMPIRE (3) races forward and deserved his 2.2L win at Wagga over a mile. Maps well and should be suited around here. Will get every chance to repeat the dose. THAT A BOY (2) is a local who draws the paint. Raced a short-priced favourite here last time over 1460m and winning rider Heywood is reunited, and that's a positive. POKER FLASH (5) peaks and the winkers go on. She was better at the mile here last time and keeps the handy 2kg claim. She has scope for further improvement.
